Subject: cio: initialization of I/O devices fails
References: BNC#563999
From: Gerald Schaefer <geraldsc@de.ibm.com>
Patch-mainline: 2.6.33-rc1
Git-commit: e1f0fbd655539b0093738f58d57db83a0ac2dd6c
Git-commit: 9679baaf85b6e4dc662160bbbca344287ea6580d

Symptom: I/O devices do not become available in Linux despite the hardware
             being available.
Problem: Not all temporary or non-fatal hardware failures during I/O device
             setup are handled correctly.
Solution: Introduce a single infrastructure for correct handling of internal
             I/O request.
